Based on the foregoing, we recommended that the management direct the concerned officials to the following courses of action:
The Municipal Accountant:
a.Prepare the Journal Voucher (JV) to record the beginning balance of the local road network and its components in the general ledger and the Local Road Network Ledger Card (Annex A), respectively;
b.Support the JV with the Registry of Public Infrastructures for Roads, working papers on the distribution of costs for the road components, and working papers on the determination of the depreciated replacement cost for road components with no available cost per registry;
c.Keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network; and
d.Include disclosures of the Local Road Network System in the Notes to Financial Statements in the aforementioned prescribed format.
The General Services Officer:
a.Maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map;
b.Conduct a physical count and prepare the Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System; 
c.Keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and their components (Annex B); and
d.Prepare the Report on the Local Road Network of the MLGU of Pigcawayan (Annex C).
Municipal Engineer: Provide the Municipal Accountant and the GSO with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.
We also recommended the management to form an inventory committee in order to properly oversee the physical count, as well as other internal control over the Plant, Property, and Equipment.

In line with the AAR observations, we recommended that the management take the following actions:
a.Require the Municipal Treasurer to prepare a certified list of tax delinquencies and conduct a reconciliation on the recorded receivables in order to establish a realistic balance of the tax receivables from the RPT and SET so that necessary adjustment(s) in the books could be reflected for the fair presentation of balances and transactions in the financial statements;
b.Require the Municipal Treasurer to prepare a duly certified list showing the name of taxpayers and the amount due and collectible for the year and furnish the Municipal Accountant with the said report to serve as the basis for the recognition of the Tax Receivables at the beginning of the year;
c.Require a periodic reconciliation between the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer of their records in order to have a proper check and balance of the reflected information in the financial statements; and,
d.Conduct extensive tax awareness campaigns to educate taxpayers on the benefits and services that the Municipality provides when taxes are paid.

