We recommended that management require the City Accountant to –
1. maintain Subsidiary Ledger (SL) for each depository account to substantiate the existence, validity and accuracy of the balances appearing in the General Ledger (GL);
2. reconcile SL of City Accounting Office and cashbook of City Treasury Office beginning the first quarter of 2019;
3. submit correct Bank Reconciliation Statement for the LBP General Fund account nos. 2012-1001-78 and 2012-1002-75, and begin the preparation of BRS for DBP Time Deposit account no. 0910-029982-100 and DBP Current account no. 0910-029982-030;
4. consider assigning more human resource to prepare BRS, preferably a Certified Public Accountant (CPA) to perform the bank reconciliation, and requesting for snapshots of bank accounts within a week after the end of the month if bank statements will cause undue delay in the preparation of BRS; and
5. prepare the BRS every month, within ten days from receipt of the Bank Statements issued by its authorized depository bank or upon receipt of requested bank snapshots, and submit promptly the BRS including the GL/SL of Cash in Bank – LCCA and Cash in Bank – LCTD accounts, supporting schedules for all reconciling items, bank statements/bank snapshots and used checks to COA for verification and audit, in accordance with COA Circular No. 96-011; and
6. carefully reconcile the balances per books with those per bank to identify the causes of huge discrepancy. Identify the items in bank debit/credit memos and book errors to be able to prepare the necessary adjusting journal entries, particularly those that have been appearing as reconciling items for so many years, and present fairly the Cash in Bank balances in the financial statements.

We recommended that management - 2018
1. ensure as far as practicable an optimum level of delivery of Bottom-Up Projects through institution of mechanisms that help achieve desirable socio-economic development and inclusive growth;
2. require each implementing division to submit quarterly accomplishment report to monitor the status of implementation of programs and projects funded by the transfers, and to ensure that funds are used for their intended purposes; 
