the GFPS formulate and identify programs, projects and activities in line with item C.2.1 of DILG-NEDA-DBM Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2013-01 that will be included in the GPB to address priority gender issues;
management prioritize the efficiency of the GAD Fund by utilizing it to purely PPAs that will help empower women and narrow the gap on gender inequality in order to deliver quality services for the constituents. Salaries of casual personnel should not be given priority unless they are working on GAD PPAs; and,
the GAD Focal Person prepare and submit the annual GAD Accomplishment Report as prescribed by PCW-DILG-NEDA-DBM JMC No. 2013-01 so that the implementation of the GAD plan and GAD-related PPAs could be monitored and evaluated.

Require the City Accountant and the City General Services Officer to maintain PPE Ledger Cards and Property Cards, respectively, for each category of asset per fund, and to conduct periodic reconciliation of their respective records to forestall possible discrepancies;

Also, require the Inventory Committee to ensure the completion of the physical inventory of all properties of the City Government observing the procedures of inventory-taking set forth in Section 491, Volume I of the Government Accounting and Auditing Manual (GAAM), in order to ascertain the existence, validity and correctness of the reported PPE in the books; and,

Further, consider creating a special task force or committee composed of experienced personnel with wide exposure on bookkeeping and accounting, whose responsibility is to perform procedures necessary to improve internal controls on the City’s assets like the preparation of PPELC and PC; to reconcile records between the City Accounting Office and City General Services Office; to assist in the proper conduct of physical inventory of PPEs as well as preparation of the same, and other duties that will ensure the proper accounting and safeguard on the assets of the City Government.
